# Branch Naming

When creating a git branch to implement changes, always name it `feature/<feature-name>`, where `<feature-name>` is a short kebab-case description of the change.

Examples:

- `feature/hitl-resume-wiring`
- `feature/drift-benchmark-expansion`
- `feature/frontend-bearer-auth`

Do not use other prefixes (e.g. `cursor/`, `fix/`, `chore/`) unless the user explicitly asks for a different name.
